markers.description: The earliest documented introduction to the Spanish court occurred in 1544, but it was not until 1585 that the first official shipment of cacao to Europe was recorded. In the 18th century, chocolate was considered southern European, aristocratic and Catholic. This was in contrast to the bourgeois coffee and proletarian alcohol.
